1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:00:00,830 --> 00:00:02,240
Use me.

3
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:04,350
I'll be your boyfriend.

4
00:00:41,050 --> 00:00:42,320
This is my girlfriend.

5
00:00:47,600 --> 00:00:48,750
She's pretty, right?

6
00:00:50,680 --> 00:00:52,970
So-bin, is this true?

7
00:00:56,400 --> 00:00:58,030
I hear you're best friends.

8
00:00:58,380 --> 00:01:01,860
My girlfriend having a male BFF
isn't that ideal for me.

9
00:01:01,950 --> 00:01:05,950
I'm afraid
there's too much history between us.

10
00:01:06,570 --> 00:01:08,460
Chan-ki, what's taking you so long?

11
00:01:10,660 --> 00:01:11,850
Her again?

12
00:01:15,190 --> 00:01:18,230
I'm afraid we won't be able to be friends.

13
00:01:32,570 --> 00:01:34,860
Come on. Aren't you coming inside?

14
00:01:34,950 --> 00:01:36,050
I'll be a minute.

15
00:01:37,190 --> 00:01:39,210
Here's my advice to you
as your ex-girlfriend.

16
00:01:39,300 --> 00:01:42,470
Unless you cut her from your life,
you'll never get a girlfriend

17
00:01:42,560 --> 00:01:43,830
or marry someone.

18
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,150
I can do without.

19
00:01:57,910 --> 00:02:00,250
What can I do for you? Just ask.

20
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:03,410
I'd rather go to my dorm room.

21
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:05,700
And cry under the covers?

22
00:02:10,850 --> 00:02:14,810
No. But...

23
00:02:14,900 --> 00:02:15,950
But what?

24
00:02:18,510 --> 00:02:20,620
I should've brought
the fried chicken with me.

25
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:22,690
For you, I mean.

26
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,630
Forget it. I hate fried chicken!

27
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:27,750
Especially what was meant
for someone else.

28
00:02:28,850 --> 00:02:31,880
Okay, fine. I'll get you
something nicer next time.

29
00:02:37,070 --> 00:02:39,930
I'll go with you then and walk you back.

30
00:02:41,079 --> 00:02:43,370
-No, don't.
-I forbid you to say that.

31
00:02:43,540 --> 00:02:46,140
I did you a favor,
so I'll do whatever I want.

32
00:02:46,970 --> 00:02:48,560
And what would that be?

33
00:02:51,070 --> 00:02:52,120
Speaking casually to you.

34
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,210
When I'm your senior?

35
00:02:56,300 --> 00:02:57,400
Is that a no?

36
00:02:59,070 --> 00:03:00,260
Well,

37
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,610
you're my mentor, so do as you wish.

38
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:08,750
Your student should oblige
since she only humiliated herself today.

39
00:03:09,330 --> 00:03:10,650
Exactly, So-bin.

40
00:03:11,170 --> 00:03:13,290
Not too casually.

41
00:03:14,340 --> 00:03:15,970
This is how it'll be!

42
00:03:16,060 --> 00:03:18,740
Hey, Yeo Jun. Jun!

43
00:03:19,010 --> 00:03:20,190
Hurry up.

44
00:03:24,550 --> 00:03:27,190
I can't believe you called
right on time though.

45
00:03:29,210 --> 00:03:30,400
Worry swept over me.

46
00:03:31,370 --> 00:03:32,650
And regret.

47
00:03:33,790 --> 00:03:34,930
Regret?

48
00:03:35,860 --> 00:03:38,010
I pushed you
into confessing your feelings.

49
00:03:39,950 --> 00:03:41,270
Stop saying that.

50
00:03:42,460 --> 00:03:43,950
You did nothing wrong.

51
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:48,000
Rejected or not,

52
00:03:49,450 --> 00:03:51,960
I should've picked another day though.

53
00:03:53,550 --> 00:03:55,300
That I regret.

54
00:03:56,230 --> 00:03:57,420
Why's that?

55
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:01,020
That ex of his

56
00:04:02,210 --> 00:04:06,480
wasn't too fond of me when they dated.

57
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,750
She told me to stay away from him.

58
00:04:12,990 --> 00:04:15,500
So I promised her.

59
00:04:17,610 --> 00:04:19,589
That I didn't like Chan-ki.

60
00:04:21,750 --> 00:04:22,940
That...

61
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:26,980
there was nothing between us.

62
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:33,580
They seem to be back together.

63
00:04:37,240 --> 00:04:39,000
Those candles I lit.

64
00:04:41,460 --> 00:04:43,130
Darn, this is humiliating.

65
00:04:45,070 --> 00:04:46,700
She knows I lied.

66
00:04:47,659 --> 00:04:50,659
Don't cry. I won't let you a second time.

67
00:05:00,030 --> 00:05:01,130
It's Chan-ki.

68
00:05:02,580 --> 00:05:03,680
Don't answer him.

69
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,440
You're forbidding everything.

70
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:07,240
Didn't I earn that right?

71
00:05:08,740 --> 00:05:10,100
As your boyfriend.

72
00:05:11,420 --> 00:05:12,350
[Chan-ki]

73
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:16,400
-Declining his call like that--
-He'll be taken aback.

74
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,240
It's why I declined it though.

75
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,190
But we're still friends.

76
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:23,740
Someone who takes advantage
of your feelings

77
00:05:23,830 --> 00:05:26,380
and stands you up all the time
isn't a friend.

78
00:05:27,090 --> 00:05:28,940
Maybe it's just you who thinks so.

79
00:05:30,210 --> 00:05:32,720
-What?
-Why do you care about a person

80
00:05:32,810 --> 00:05:34,390
who ignores and hurts you?

81
00:05:35,010 --> 00:05:36,810
Why let him own you?

82
00:05:40,990 --> 00:05:42,050
That's...

83
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,500
Of course.

84
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:46,490
It was probably your only option.

85
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:50,280
It's not easy

86
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:53,710
to find someone who can save you

87
00:05:56,300 --> 00:05:57,930
from affection deprivation.

88
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,350
Talk about a punch to the heart.

89
00:06:08,760 --> 00:06:10,160
It hurts.

90
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,200
I'm just as messed up.

91
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:17,640
How so? Are you in a one-sided love too?

92
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,760
I told you to stay clear from it.

93
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:24,460
I'll heed your advice, so you heed mine.

94
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:25,520
As in?

95
00:06:25,610 --> 00:06:27,630
Don't answer his calls

96
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,660
until he apologizes.

97
00:06:30,180 --> 00:06:31,590
Even if you do pick up,

98
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:34,280
don't agree to meet him.

99
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:35,900
Not without my permission.

100
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,780
What if I run into him?

101
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:44,480
Take a page out of Nam Soo-hyun's book.

102
00:06:46,460 --> 00:06:47,960
That's not easy to do.

103
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:50,600
Repeat after me.

104
00:06:52,890 --> 00:06:54,430
"What business do you have with me?"

105
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:56,890
"Can you get lost?"

106
00:06:58,480 --> 00:06:59,620
"Why are you laughing?"

107
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:02,300
You sound just like him.

108
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,780
"Can you get lost?"

109
00:07:07,410 --> 00:07:08,600
"Do I sound like him?"

110
00:07:09,340 --> 00:07:11,680
-"Isn't it this?"
-"Do I sound similar?"

111
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:15,900
That's how you would say it!

112
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:17,970
Sound more like Soo-hyun.

113
00:07:18,060 --> 00:07:19,160
Soo-hyun...

114
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:31,650
[World's Greatest Convenience Store]

115
00:07:49,780 --> 00:07:50,970
That'll be 2,800 won.

116
00:07:58,890 --> 00:08:00,070
Here you go.

117
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:10,770
[So-bin]

118
00:08:06,890 --> 00:08:09,310
[Good night. And don't cry again.]

119
00:08:10,850 --> 00:08:16,090
[So-bin]

120
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:15,470
[Good night.]

121
00:08:51,690 --> 00:08:52,790
Soo-hyun.

122
00:08:53,620 --> 00:08:55,820
Soo-hyun, it's been a while.

123
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,190
Park Hyung-min?

124
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,300
It's nice to run into you like this.

125
00:09:04,180 --> 00:09:06,820
We used to be close back in freshman year.

126
00:09:06,950 --> 00:09:09,240
Were we? I don't remember.

127
00:09:10,340 --> 00:09:12,850
It's been a while.
Anyway, I have somewhere to be.

128
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:16,330
Are you perhaps interested
in a part-time job?

129
00:09:19,190 --> 00:09:20,290
A part-time job?

130
00:09:20,370 --> 00:09:21,610
[Mid-term Lecture Evaluation]

131
00:09:24,550 --> 00:09:25,740
[Resume: Nam Soo-hyun]

132
00:09:27,460 --> 00:09:30,890
You've worked
all kinds of part-time jobs before

133
00:09:31,110 --> 00:09:33,130
and have a high TOEIC score.

134
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:34,590
Is it true

135
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:38,550
that you provide room and board too?

136
00:09:38,630 --> 00:09:41,540
Of course. Can you start tomorrow?

137
00:09:41,890 --> 00:09:42,990
Yes.

138
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:47,350
I look forward to the work.

139
00:09:48,010 --> 00:09:52,710
By the way, how do you know the CEO?

140
00:09:53,420 --> 00:09:54,650
The CEO?

141
00:09:55,660 --> 00:10:00,940
[Yield]

142
00:09:57,730 --> 00:09:58,830
There you go.

143
00:10:00,550 --> 00:10:02,970
-Just a second.
-Right there.

144
00:10:01,340 --> 00:10:02,660
[Under Construction, Slow Down]

145
00:10:05,470 --> 00:10:07,850
-That'd be 250.
-Can you pull on that side?

146
00:10:07,940 --> 00:10:10,490
Miss, you can't go in there!

147
00:10:18,010 --> 00:10:20,080
[Under Construction, Slow Down]

148
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:26,590
Young-ran.

149
00:10:26,950 --> 00:10:29,150
[Safety First]

150
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:31,960
Tell me. Why did you turn down that job?

151
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,070
It was a good one.

152
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,880
The kind you were looking for.

153
00:10:35,970 --> 00:10:38,470
And how exactly would you know that?

154
00:10:39,490 --> 00:10:41,990
-What?
-A job like that never existed.

155
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:44,190
I heard that

156
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:46,090
someone asked the CEO to make an opening.

157
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:51,410
No wonder.
It had a room and board arrangement,

158
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:54,270
the job was easy,
and it paid way too much.

159
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:56,290
Moreover,

160
00:10:56,380 --> 00:10:58,760
someone I barely know offered me the gig.

161
00:10:59,240 --> 00:11:00,560
Come to think of it,

162
00:11:01,790 --> 00:11:03,550
he had a crush on you since freshman year.

163
00:11:03,640 --> 00:11:04,960
So what?

164
00:11:05,050 --> 00:11:06,810
Friends can pull some strings, you know.

165
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:08,090
Because you are my friend.

166
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,270
Because of me, you're in his debt.

167
00:11:13,190 --> 00:11:14,420
How will you repay him?

168
00:11:15,610 --> 00:11:16,750
Young-ran,

169
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:18,950
I hate being in people's debts.

170
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,080
I loathe being a problem to others.

171
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,980
I don't know how to repay favors.

172
00:11:26,260 --> 00:11:28,500
Nor do I have the ability or time.

173
00:11:29,030 --> 00:11:30,220
I just...

174
00:11:31,980 --> 00:11:34,270
I just wanted to cut you a break.

175
00:11:46,410 --> 00:11:51,820
[Young-ran]

176
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:57,850
[Did I say I wanted to die?]

177
00:11:58,460 --> 00:11:59,830
I suppose you say that often

178
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:02,600
without knowing
what it's really like to want to die.

179
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:22,800
[Youth Villa]

180
00:12:36,660 --> 00:12:37,710
[Marketing Team Project]

181
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:40,260
[I forgot I had a tutoring job]

182
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:45,630
[So-bin]

183
00:12:40,350 --> 00:12:41,800
[and asked us to gather.]

184
00:12:42,420 --> 00:12:43,700
[I'm really sorry.]

185
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,600
[Soo-hyun, can you]

186
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:52,980
[So-bin]

187
00:12:46,690 --> 00:12:49,240
[gather the materials
and go over them instead?]

188
00:12:50,030 --> 00:12:52,140
[I'm really, really, really sorry.]

189
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:56,060
Maybe I should skip school today.

190
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:04,160
[Can't you tell the time?]

191
00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:06,490
I'm only ten minutes late.

192
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:07,720
[Just ten minutes?]

193
00:13:08,250 --> 00:13:09,740
[I told you to be on time.]

194
00:13:09,830 --> 00:13:12,120
[Being punctual is the first step
to acing tests.]

195
00:13:12,210 --> 00:13:14,450
[-Ten minutes is enough to--]
-I think I'm lost.

196
00:13:15,160 --> 00:13:17,000
I'm at the fountain, so meet me here.

197
00:13:17,090 --> 00:13:18,150
Bye!

198
00:13:19,120 --> 00:13:20,350
Such a nagger.

199
00:13:20,830 --> 00:13:22,900
I took time off practice

200
00:13:22,990 --> 00:13:25,360
to meet him between his classes.

201
00:13:29,410 --> 00:13:31,080
He'll be a while, right?

202
00:13:31,170 --> 00:13:32,450
Let's take a look around.

203
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:38,430
Him over there.

204
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:41,070
Seriously? Not again.

205
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:43,840
Bleaching your hair
damages your roots and scalp.

206
00:13:43,930 --> 00:13:45,560
Is it your roots or scalp though?

207
00:13:45,650 --> 00:13:47,940
-Mind your own business.
-I know from experience.

208
00:13:48,950 --> 00:13:50,000
Soo-kyung,

209
00:13:50,750 --> 00:13:52,200
you think I'm a boomer.

210
00:13:52,820 --> 00:13:54,890
I'm most certainly not.

211
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:56,340
Then what are you?

212
00:13:56,870 --> 00:14:00,260
All I wish
is to talk about life with students

213
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:02,540
over a meal.

214
00:14:02,850 --> 00:14:06,680
There's so much I've experienced
that I want to tell them about.

215
00:14:07,740 --> 00:14:09,540
That's what makes you a boomer.

216
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,380
It sure is hot outside.

217
00:15:10,660 --> 00:15:11,760
What is he doing?

218
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:13,430
Can you believe it?

219
00:15:16,420 --> 00:15:18,660
-Unbelievable.
-He's not that good though.

220
00:15:19,320 --> 00:15:21,130
-Why isn't he getting up?
-He's good.

221
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:28,960
Soo-hyun!

222
00:15:38,380 --> 00:15:39,910
We're in matching colors today.

223
00:15:40,490 --> 00:15:41,810
Did you copy my look?

224
00:15:47,310 --> 00:15:49,640
Take your pants off too
while you're at it.

225
00:15:50,030 --> 00:15:52,100
Stride in your underwear.

226
00:15:52,890 --> 00:15:54,650
You have a unique talent.

227
00:15:54,740 --> 00:15:57,340
What would that be?
I have so many, you see.

228
00:15:58,090 --> 00:16:00,150
You ignore what others say

229
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:02,350
and get in their faces with a smile.

230
00:16:03,940 --> 00:16:05,390
Not to everyone, you know.

231
00:16:09,920 --> 00:16:11,240
Just like you said,

232
00:16:11,330 --> 00:16:13,750
I'm more like this
because you're hard to win over.

233
00:16:14,320 --> 00:16:17,090
I just think
you're being pretentious like me.

234
00:16:18,410 --> 00:16:19,510
Pretentious?

235
00:16:20,260 --> 00:16:22,370
I laugh in people’s faces

236
00:16:22,460 --> 00:16:25,280
and it seems like
you’re trying hard not to like me.

237
00:16:25,630 --> 00:16:26,910
Isn’t that being pretentious too?

238
00:16:28,450 --> 00:16:29,680
Hey, you laughed!

239
00:16:33,290 --> 00:16:36,150
I don't know
why I'm trying to patronize you,

240
00:16:36,760 --> 00:16:37,860
but listen up.

241
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:42,260
In this world,
there are people who don't like you.

242
00:16:44,370 --> 00:16:45,470
That's true.

243
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:48,470
But I don't think you're not one of them.

244
00:16:50,310 --> 00:16:51,460
I apologize.

245
00:16:51,550 --> 00:16:53,570
I could see right through you

246
00:16:53,660 --> 00:16:55,460
which is why I bothered to converse.

247
00:16:55,810 --> 00:16:57,000
But, just forget about it.

248
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,760
You know how I am

249
00:16:58,850 --> 00:17:00,480
and I treat everyone the same.

250
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:05,270
You can apologize

251
00:17:07,250 --> 00:17:09,230
by treating me to a meal.

252
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,490
No one has ever
been treated to one by you,

253
00:17:13,060 --> 00:17:14,380
and I'd like to be your first.

254
00:17:15,260 --> 00:17:17,990
You won't agree to a meal that I buy,

255
00:17:18,079 --> 00:17:20,720
-so treat me to one instead.
-Why would I?

256
00:17:27,450 --> 00:17:29,210
You've got to be kidding me.

257
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:43,640
Look at him.
He can't take his eyes off Mi-ju.

258
00:17:44,610 --> 00:17:46,500
You haven't found a model yet, have you?

259
00:17:47,210 --> 00:17:48,920
-What about him?
-Forget it.

260
00:17:49,450 --> 00:17:52,570
Excuse me.
Are you perhaps interested in modeling?

261
00:17:52,660 --> 00:17:54,330
Sorry? A model?

262
00:17:54,420 --> 00:17:57,370
-Don't.
-She's looking for one.

263
00:17:57,810 --> 00:17:59,570
You'll be seeing her at least once a week.

264
00:17:59,660 --> 00:18:02,250
What? Every week? With her?

265
00:18:02,340 --> 00:18:04,760
-Stop it.
-Do you think you can handle it?

266
00:18:04,850 --> 00:18:07,710
Of course.
I'm confident in the body I carry.

267
00:18:08,370 --> 00:18:09,600
Why don't I show you?

268
00:18:12,110 --> 00:18:13,470
What do you think you're doing?

269
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:15,670
Soo-hyun, it's...

270
00:18:21,040 --> 00:18:22,100
Let's go.

271
00:18:22,850 --> 00:18:23,900
Just a second!

272
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,520
Did I ask you to strip?

