What are you doing to my friend?

538
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:37,450
Did you pass the exam or something?

539
00:35:38,020 --> 00:35:40,360
You need to learn to enjoy
the small things in life.

540
00:35:40,440 --> 00:35:42,200
You're always so serious.

541
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:45,500
Just pass the exam, please.

542
00:35:50,120 --> 00:35:51,970
Let go!

543
00:35:53,340 --> 00:35:55,710
-What is it?
-It's nothing.

544
00:36:03,150 --> 00:36:04,290
It's cash.

545
00:36:05,170 --> 00:36:06,400
Where did you get this?

546
00:36:07,500 --> 00:36:08,820
Come on. It's just 100,000 won.

547
00:36:08,910 --> 00:36:10,670
Hey, "just 100,000 won"?

548
00:36:11,290 --> 00:36:13,840
You always work so hard,
so I did some gig work just for the day.

549
00:36:14,540 --> 00:36:15,910
You'd better tell me the truth.

550
00:36:16,000 --> 00:36:19,340
Hey, just let it go. It's really nothing.

551
00:36:19,430 --> 00:36:20,530
Nam Koo-hyun.

552
00:36:21,540 --> 00:36:25,370
Well, I just sold something
I got for free.

553
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:33,070
From your rich friend.

554
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:36,020
-Yeo Jun?
-Yes.

555
00:36:36,410 --> 00:36:38,300
I told him I liked his watch,

556
00:36:38,390 --> 00:36:39,710
and he said I could have it.

557
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,650
-And you accepted it?
-Hey.

558
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:43,140
Of course, I did. It's expensive.

559
00:36:43,230 --> 00:36:44,820
Are you a beggar?

560
00:36:44,900 --> 00:36:46,270
That's a mean thing to say.

561
00:36:46,360 --> 00:36:48,860
What's wrong with accepting something
he doesn't need?

562
00:36:52,250 --> 00:36:53,400
Is this it?

563
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:55,290
It's what's left
after paying for the gosiwon.

564
00:36:55,380 --> 00:36:56,430
Hey!

565
00:36:59,510 --> 00:37:03,820
[Youth Villa]

566
00:37:07,740 --> 00:37:10,200
-Soo-hyun?
-[I'm in front of your place. Come out.]

567
00:37:10,640 --> 00:37:11,700
Now?

568
00:37:11,790 --> 00:37:14,300
Yes, I'll wait here until you come out.

569
00:37:15,750 --> 00:37:17,330
Okay, give me a minute.

570
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:28,330
Soo-hyun.

571
00:37:31,020 --> 00:37:32,510
Koo-hyun told me what happened.

572
00:37:33,390 --> 00:37:34,930
Oh, that.

573
00:37:36,120 --> 00:37:38,940
-Why did you do that?
-I gave it to him because he wanted it.

574
00:37:39,420 --> 00:37:40,700
I can just buy another one.

575
00:37:45,710 --> 00:37:46,860
I'm sorry.

576
00:37:48,090 --> 00:37:49,190
For what?

577
00:37:49,940 --> 00:37:52,490
I can't pay you back right away,
but I will.

578
00:37:52,580 --> 00:37:54,070
Will that make you feel at ease?

579
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:59,620
You said I'd call you.
Were you referring to this?

580
00:38:02,340 --> 00:38:05,250
-Did I say that?
-So, it all went according to your plan.

581
00:38:06,040 --> 00:38:08,200
You made me call you first
and practically beg you.

582
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,740
That wasn't my plan.

583
00:38:11,140 --> 00:38:12,860
You may never have found out.

584
00:38:17,830 --> 00:38:19,200
What do you want from me?

585
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:21,750
What could it be?

586
00:38:23,420 --> 00:38:24,650
Forget about the money.

587
00:38:25,580 --> 00:38:26,900
I don't need money.

588
00:38:27,420 --> 00:38:28,830
As you know, I can get it easily.

589
00:38:31,430 --> 00:38:32,790
Can you warm up to me?

590
00:38:35,960 --> 00:38:38,200
Nobody warms up to you
because they genuinely like you

591
00:38:39,130 --> 00:38:42,650
without you having you trick them
like this or spend money on them?

592
00:38:48,410 --> 00:38:49,510
That's right.

593
00:38:51,180 --> 00:38:52,460
Nobody.

594
00:38:58,880 --> 00:39:00,070
Don't you pity me?

595
00:39:04,030 --> 00:39:05,350
Don't look at me like that.

596
00:39:06,500 --> 00:39:08,120
You need money,

597
00:39:08,210 --> 00:39:10,100
and I need love. It's the same thing.

598
00:39:11,070 --> 00:39:13,050
You do everything in your power
to earn money.

599
00:39:14,190 --> 00:39:16,920
I'm just doing what I want to do
to get what I want.

600
00:39:23,040 --> 00:39:24,180
All right.

601
00:39:25,370 --> 00:39:27,480
You won. I'll do as you say.

602
00:39:31,180 --> 00:39:32,450
Answer my calls.

603
00:39:34,170 --> 00:39:35,310
I'll head in, then.

604
00:39:55,470 --> 00:39:56,740
Kim So-bin!

605
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:01,850
So-bin, Kim So-bin.

606
00:40:03,690 --> 00:40:05,320
So-bin, are you mad at me?

607
00:40:05,940 --> 00:40:07,610
I knew you had your tutoring session here,

608
00:40:07,700 --> 00:40:09,190
so I came to pick you up.

609
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:10,690
Who has such an amazing friend?

610
00:40:11,220 --> 00:40:12,540
You do!

611
00:40:13,370 --> 00:40:15,440
So-bin, don't be mad at me.

612
00:40:15,840 --> 00:40:17,110
Leave me alone, please.

613
00:40:17,380 --> 00:40:19,310
Why did you have to come by that day?

614
00:40:19,400 --> 00:40:20,850
Someone told me

615
00:40:20,940 --> 00:40:22,830
that was the best day to go to your place,

616
00:40:23,540 --> 00:40:24,950
but I ended up humiliating myself.

617
00:40:25,340 --> 00:40:26,710
Who told you that?

618
00:40:27,670 --> 00:40:29,650
Don't tell me... Yeo Jun?

619
00:40:31,330 --> 00:40:32,510
That's right!

620
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:35,150
My boyfriend said
that promises must be kept

621
00:40:35,240 --> 00:40:36,520
and told me to go that day.

622
00:40:38,450 --> 00:40:40,790
Are you actually seeing him?

623
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,590
You're joking, right?

624
00:40:43,910 --> 00:40:45,710
-That's...
-You're not seeing him, right?

625
00:40:46,510 --> 00:40:49,190
Right, no way! I knew it.

626
00:40:50,250 --> 00:40:51,430
"I knew it"?

627
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:54,730
-What I meant was...
-What did you mean by that?

628
00:40:54,820 --> 00:40:57,420
Were you saying I shouldn't even dream
of dating a guy like him?

629
00:40:59,570 --> 00:41:00,980
Now, I'm relieved.

630
00:41:01,070 --> 00:41:02,790
Yes, this is the So-bin I know.

631
00:41:02,870 --> 00:41:05,210
The timid, sensitive girl
who can only yell at me.

632
00:41:05,290 --> 00:41:07,010
This is the Kim So-bin I know.

633
00:41:09,080 --> 00:41:10,620
Hey, were you not joking?

634
00:41:11,410 --> 00:41:13,740
Hey! We've stayed friends
even after I got a girlfriend.

635
00:41:13,830 --> 00:41:15,630
Why let that jerk ruin our friendship?

636
00:41:16,030 --> 00:41:17,090
"That jerk"?

637
00:41:17,170 --> 00:41:19,550
Don't call him like that.

638
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,000
Don't trust him.

639
00:41:29,100 --> 00:41:32,000
He knew I'd have a girl over that day.

640
00:41:33,980 --> 00:41:35,210
I told him.

641
00:41:39,570 --> 00:41:40,710
So what?

642
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:43,660
Are you saying he told me to go over
to your place that day on purpose?

643
00:41:44,150 --> 00:41:45,640
That's absurd.

644
00:41:54,570 --> 00:41:59,810
[Yeo Jun]

645
00:41:57,610 --> 00:42:00,250
[Why don't you tell him tomorrow?]

646
00:42:02,100 --> 00:42:04,210
[If he says no, just come meet me now.]

647
00:42:04,300 --> 00:42:06,720
I can't believe you called
right on time though.

648
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:08,430
Worry swept over me.

649
00:42:09,490 --> 00:42:10,630
And regret.

650
00:42:12,570 --> 00:42:14,770
He's been kind of creeping me out.

651
00:42:15,300 --> 00:42:17,890
People like him aren't good for you
because you trust others easily

652
00:42:17,980 --> 00:42:18,990
and tell them everything.

653
00:42:19,080 --> 00:42:20,530
But you don't even know him well.

654
00:42:21,850 --> 00:42:23,920
I know a lot more about Jun than you do.

655
00:42:31,140 --> 00:42:34,530
So, you are serious about this.

656
00:42:39,890 --> 00:42:41,040
Yes.

657
00:42:44,780 --> 00:42:45,970
No more crush.

658
00:42:48,080 --> 00:42:49,220
It's over now.

659
00:42:52,210 --> 00:42:53,400
What about us as friends?

660
00:42:56,480 --> 00:42:59,030
Not sure. I don't know.

661
00:43:01,590 --> 00:43:03,560
I want to focus on myself now.

662
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:29,300
[Don't trust him.]

663
00:43:29,790 --> 00:43:32,870
He knew I'd have a girl over that day.

664
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:37,800
[Please, I hope I'm wrong.]

665
00:43:44,220 --> 00:43:47,260
[Nam Soo-hyun]

666
00:44:04,770 --> 00:44:05,960
Hey, where are you?

667
00:44:06,880 --> 00:44:08,160
Hi, Jun.

668
00:44:09,210 --> 00:44:12,070
Can we meet now?

669
00:44:19,680 --> 00:44:21,050
You call this a nice place?

670
00:44:21,440 --> 00:44:23,420
To me, it is.

671
00:44:25,620 --> 00:44:28,750
I'll go easy on you
since you asked me to meet up first.

672
00:44:30,770 --> 00:44:33,940
Well... Jun.

673
00:44:34,510 --> 00:44:35,610
Yes?

674
00:44:35,880 --> 00:44:37,810
I had such a long day today.

675
00:44:37,900 --> 00:44:39,260
Soo-hyun and Jung-ho...

676
00:44:39,350 --> 00:44:41,200
You can tell me about that later.

677
00:44:43,440 --> 00:44:46,920
I want to ask you something.

678
00:44:49,380 --> 00:44:50,840
What is it? You can ask me anything.

679
00:44:55,500 --> 00:44:56,600
You know,

680
00:44:58,670 --> 00:45:01,840
that day... The day I went
to Chan-ki's place to tell him how I feel.

681
00:45:02,980 --> 00:45:04,700
Did you know

682
00:45:05,930 --> 00:45:08,170
that his girlfriend would be over
that day?

683
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:14,200
Do you think I intentionally made you
run into her?

684
00:45:16,090 --> 00:45:17,240
No.

685
00:45:18,250 --> 00:45:19,440
Did you

686
00:45:21,370 --> 00:45:22,560
see him?

687
00:45:22,740 --> 00:45:23,790
Yes.

688
00:45:25,550 --> 00:45:27,710
He came to pick me up
after my tutoring session.

689
00:45:33,870 --> 00:45:35,190
Forget it, if that's not the case.

690
00:45:36,330 --> 00:45:38,220
To tell you the truth,

691
00:45:38,880 --> 00:45:41,040
I did wonder if you did it on purpose.

692
00:45:42,320 --> 00:45:43,460
I'm sorry.

693
00:45:45,180 --> 00:45:46,320
I did.

694
00:45:49,310 --> 00:45:52,790
-What?
-I sent you there because I knew about it.

695
00:45:54,110 --> 00:45:56,090
I wasn't sure whether
the timing would work out,

696
00:45:57,850 --> 00:45:59,120
but I thought it could.

697
00:46:03,790 --> 00:46:05,370
What you were wondering is true.

698
00:46:08,280 --> 00:46:09,380
Why did you do that?

699
00:46:09,460 --> 00:46:11,000
I wanted to end it for you.

700
00:46:11,580 --> 00:46:14,390
I'm sure it's hard for you
to keep getting disappointed.

701
00:46:14,790 --> 00:46:16,060
Was that the only way though?

702
00:46:16,150 --> 00:46:17,340
It'd help you give up quickly.

703
00:46:17,470 --> 00:46:19,720
Are you sure
you didn't want to see me get hurt?

704
00:46:19,800 --> 00:46:22,310
Was it fun for you to watch me cry
like an idiot?

705
00:46:37,270 --> 00:46:39,430
So he rejected you,
just as I had expected.

706
00:46:40,660 --> 00:46:44,140
You should've stopped being so foolish
a long time ago.

707
00:46:45,900 --> 00:46:47,480
Didn't I tell you?

708
00:46:51,790 --> 00:46:53,420
You told me to use you.

709
00:46:55,660 --> 00:46:56,810
What did you mean by that?

710
00:46:56,900 --> 00:46:58,830
I hurt you,

711
00:47:00,240 --> 00:47:02,260
so it's only right
that you gain something from me.

712
00:47:04,330 --> 00:47:05,300
Yeo Jun.

713
00:47:05,390 --> 00:47:07,150
That's the only thing
I've learned in life.

714
00:47:07,940 --> 00:47:09,130
Give and take.

715
00:47:10,310 --> 00:47:12,510
Nothing's free in life.

716
00:47:13,920 --> 00:47:16,170
I was bound to get hurt
even if you didn't get involved.

717
00:47:16,690 --> 00:47:18,450
I'm not trying to put the blame on you.

718
00:47:21,310 --> 00:47:22,630
But I can't figure you out.

719
00:47:25,190 --> 00:47:26,420
You scare me.

720
00:47:31,740 --> 00:47:33,770
I don't think I can be friends with you
anymore.

721
00:47:36,010 --> 00:47:37,150
We'll just be

722
00:47:38,390 --> 00:47:39,930
teammates from now on.

723
00:47:43,930 --> 00:47:45,160
I'm off.

724
00:48:32,020 --> 00:48:33,740
[But you have to keep your promise too.]

725
00:48:33,830 --> 00:48:36,030
You promised we'll be close friends
if I gave you my spot.

726
00:48:36,110 --> 00:48:38,450
You'll do a good job, so don't worry.

727
00:48:39,900 --> 00:48:41,920
[It'll be thrilling
since you'll be working with me.]

728
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:45,970
[This is my girlfriend.]

729
00:48:49,310 --> 00:48:50,410
She's pretty, right?

730
00:48:50,990 --> 00:48:52,610
[Didn't I earn that right?]

731
00:48:52,700 --> 00:48:54,590
As your boyfriend.

732
00:49:42,690 --> 00:49:45,060
[So he rejected you,
just as I had expected.]

733
00:49:46,120 --> 00:49:49,510
You should've stopped being so foolish
a long time ago.

734
00:50:11,510 --> 00:50:13,130
[Lee Hye-ra]

735
00:50:18,990 --> 00:50:21,410
Okay, let's meet up.

736
00:51:16,540 --> 00:51:19,620
Do you want to come up? I booked a room.

737
00:51:43,820 --> 00:51:45,400
[Road Closed, Detour]

738
00:52:07,270 --> 00:52:08,900
[Yeo Jun]

739
00:52:17,560 --> 00:52:20,070
-[Soo-hyun.]
-Hey.

740
00:52:20,820 --> 00:52:21,920
You picked up.

741
00:52:22,540 --> 00:52:24,430
[Of course. I still owe you.]

742
00:52:29,140 --> 00:52:30,410
[I'm working.]

743
00:52:32,830 --> 00:52:35,080
-At such a late time?
-Yes. At such a late time.

744
00:52:38,420 --> 00:52:40,490
I hurt someone

745
00:52:41,760 --> 00:52:44,050
and I want to know
how to go back to the way things were.

746
00:52:44,180 --> 00:52:46,520
[What are you doing over there?
Get back to work!]

747
00:52:46,600 --> 00:52:47,660
[Yes, sir.]

748
00:52:52,980 --> 00:52:55,710
[Just tell her how you feel
without embellishing.]

749
00:52:58,310 --> 00:53:01,040
-That's it?
-You're bad at that.

750
00:53:02,000 --> 00:53:04,030
Just do what you're bad at.

751
00:53:04,730 --> 00:53:05,880
[Bye.]

752
00:53:48,250 --> 00:53:49,700
I must be out of my mind.

753
00:53:49,790 --> 00:53:51,240
Why am I doing this?

754
00:53:51,330 --> 00:53:53,310
Hey, good actions lead to good fortune.

755
00:53:53,400 --> 00:53:55,290
Do you want me to die of muscle cramps?

756
00:53:55,380 --> 00:53:56,700
Do you have to say it like that?

757
00:53:56,780 --> 00:53:58,190
Why do you get so many cramps?

758
00:53:58,280 --> 00:54:00,000
Because I work my butt off
to make a living.

759
00:54:00,080 --> 00:54:02,110
It's probably because
you're drinking all the time.

760
00:54:02,200 --> 00:54:03,870
[So-bin!]

761
00:54:05,100 --> 00:54:07,120
Hey, did you hear that?

762
00:54:09,460 --> 00:54:11,350
[-So-bin!]
-Who is that?

763
00:54:15,440 --> 00:54:17,380
-Yeo Jun?
-So-bin!

764
00:54:18,080 --> 00:54:19,660
Did he follow me here?

765
00:54:19,750 --> 00:54:21,780
Why do you think it's you?
Maybe he's looking for me.

766
00:54:23,670 --> 00:54:24,940
-It's not you!
-It's not you!

767
00:54:29,390 --> 00:54:30,580
Gosh...

768
00:54:45,360 --> 00:54:47,910
-What are you doing here?
-I missed you.

769
00:54:49,190 --> 00:54:50,510
Am I a joke to you?

770
00:54:51,430 --> 00:54:53,940
I came because I didn't want things
to get out of hand. Just go.

771
00:54:54,030 --> 00:54:55,390
I wanted to tell you how I feel.

772
00:54:55,480 --> 00:54:59,090
So everything I heard until now
had nothing to do with your feelings?

773
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:00,630
Yes.

774
00:55:01,900 --> 00:55:03,180
Please give me a chance.

775
00:55:04,810 --> 00:55:05,910
No.

776
00:55:07,180 --> 00:55:09,950
I don't want to hear this.
I won't be fooled anymore.

777
00:55:10,920 --> 00:55:12,420
Telling you how I feel

778
00:55:14,490 --> 00:55:15,850
is awkward and difficult for me

779
00:55:19,630 --> 00:55:21,040
because I worry that you'll hate me.

780
00:55:23,200 --> 00:55:24,960
Because love is something
you have to earn.

781
00:55:30,460 --> 00:55:32,970
When I saw you have a hard time
with your crush

782
00:55:34,020 --> 00:55:35,390
it felt like I was seeing myself.

783
00:55:37,370 --> 00:55:39,570
I wanted to see that you couldn't
succeed even if you try

784
00:55:40,310 --> 00:55:41,990
when I couldn't give up myself.

785
00:55:44,320 --> 00:55:46,560
I thought I had control over everything

786
00:55:47,400 --> 00:55:51,140
when I had no idea
I couldn't even control my feelings.

787
00:55:56,510 --> 00:55:57,870
What are your feelings?

788
00:55:58,660 --> 00:56:00,730
The moment I saw your tears I realized

789
00:56:02,270 --> 00:56:04,290
what I did was wrong.

790
00:56:05,970 --> 00:56:09,790
I realized if the girl I like is in pain,
it hurts me too.

791
00:56:12,040 --> 00:56:13,270
I never knew that before.

792
00:56:17,410 --> 00:56:20,350
I'm sorry I hurt you. I truly am.

793
00:56:25,680 --> 00:56:27,000
-But...
-Next time.

794
00:56:28,540 --> 00:56:29,770
I'll hear your answer next time.

795
00:56:30,960 --> 00:56:32,100
I'm scared.

796
00:56:39,410 --> 00:56:41,780
If you're going to be informal,
just keep being informal.

797
00:56:43,540 --> 00:56:44,770
Just choose one.

798
00:56:48,070 --> 00:56:49,170
I'll be off now.

799
00:57:33,920 --> 00:57:35,680
-What's going on?
-Hey kid!

800
00:57:37,050 --> 00:57:38,590
-What's the matter?
-What happened?

801
00:57:38,670 --> 00:57:40,260
He just passed out.

802
00:57:40,350 --> 00:57:42,770
-Are you okay?
-Call an ambulance! Hurry!

803
00:57:49,850 --> 00:57:50,770
[Soo-hyun]

804
00:57:54,870 --> 00:57:56,760
-Hey, Soo-hyun.
[-Hello?]

805
00:57:58,910 --> 00:58:00,500
Isn't this Soo-hyun's phone?

806
00:58:00,590 --> 00:58:02,300
[I'm calling from
the ER at Hosu Hospital.]

807
00:58:04,720 --> 00:58:05,870
What?

808
00:58:12,070 --> 00:58:14,360
Sir, can you please go faster?

809
00:58:23,110 --> 00:58:24,210
Dad...

810
00:58:37,850 --> 00:58:39,570
Is Mr. Nam Soo-hyun's guardian here?

811
00:58:40,230 --> 00:58:41,330
Yes.

812
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:07,550
-Soo-hyun.
-What happened?

813
00:59:08,210 --> 00:59:09,800
-Are you okay?
-Why are you here?

814
00:59:09,880 --> 00:59:11,950
Do you remember collapsing
at the construction site?

815
00:59:17,140 --> 00:59:18,420
They said you have malnutrition.

816
00:59:21,100 --> 00:59:24,050
Didn't you hear me? You have malnutrition.

817
00:59:24,140 --> 00:59:25,460
I don't care.

818
00:59:26,210 --> 00:59:28,850
I'm going to call your brother and mother.

819
00:59:29,160 --> 00:59:31,140
I heard that
you told them not to call your family

820
00:59:31,220 --> 00:59:32,630
when you were rushed to the ER.

821
00:59:35,050 --> 00:59:36,500
What are you doing here?

822
00:59:41,260 --> 00:59:43,940
I called you and a nurse
at the hospital picked up.

823
00:59:44,160 --> 00:59:46,050
Why did you call me again?

824
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:48,030
What am I, your girlfriend?

825
00:59:50,190 --> 00:59:51,510
I wanted to thank you.

826
00:59:53,620 --> 00:59:55,120
Thanks to your advice,

827
00:59:55,200 --> 00:59:57,100
I got the courage to tell her how I feel.

828
00:59:58,990 --> 01:00:00,130
Good.

829
01:00:01,540 --> 01:00:04,310
Thanks for coming to the hospital
and not calling my family.

830
01:00:05,630 --> 01:00:08,050
I keep owing you. I don't know
when I'll be able to repay you.

831
01:00:08,540 --> 01:00:10,030
Do you have to repay me?

832
01:00:11,880 --> 01:00:13,200
Aren't you that kind of guy?

833
01:00:14,170 --> 01:00:16,240
When you spend money,
you expect something in return.

834
01:00:18,570 --> 01:00:19,620
I was.

835
01:00:21,430 --> 01:00:24,330
But I'm going to change.

836
01:00:26,270 --> 01:00:27,540
Go ahead and change all you want.

837
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:30,180
Go. It's getting late.

838
01:00:31,240 --> 01:00:32,910
Why are you always so angry with me?

839
01:00:34,580 --> 01:00:35,730
I know.

840
01:00:37,660 --> 01:00:39,250
Every time I see you, I just get angry.

841
01:00:40,740 --> 01:00:42,420
I guess it's because my life sucks.

842
01:00:43,520 --> 01:00:45,720
I don't even have time
to think about things like that,

843
01:00:45,800 --> 01:00:47,520
but when I see you
I feel envious and angry.

844
01:00:51,130 --> 01:00:52,270
Happy?

845
01:00:55,530 --> 01:00:56,890
-I feel the same way.
-Just go

846
01:00:57,510 --> 01:00:59,530
and stay out of my sight.

847
01:01:03,800 --> 01:01:04,940
No.

848
01:01:06,480 --> 01:01:08,110
I'm going to do what I'm good at

849
01:01:08,550 --> 01:01:10,000
so you do the same.

850
01:01:12,030 --> 01:01:13,520
What are you good at?

851
01:01:14,270 --> 01:01:16,740
-Being clingy.
-What?

852
01:01:17,220 --> 01:01:18,580
So you try to push me away.

853
01:01:19,510 --> 01:01:21,220
Let's each do what we're good at.

854
01:01:56,950 --> 01:01:59,680
[At a Distance, Spring is Green]

855
01:02:00,780 --> 01:02:03,070
[No, don't do this, So-bin.
It'll only get you killed.]

856
01:02:03,160 --> 01:02:05,440
[I heard you're going out with Jun.
Is that true?]

857
01:02:05,530 --> 01:02:07,640
I'm going to call you
"honey" and "sweetie".

858
01:02:07,730 --> 01:02:09,670
[You think this will make me
stay away from you?]

859
01:02:09,760 --> 01:02:11,380
It's going to make me miss you for sure!

860
01:02:11,470 --> 01:02:13,720
[You remind me of my brother
and it pains me.]

861
01:02:14,020 --> 01:02:15,920
Unfortunately, you are my brother.

862
01:02:16,220 --> 01:02:18,420
[So you want me
to stop being curious or clingy?]

863
01:02:18,510 --> 01:02:20,360
You called to tell me
to get out of your sight?

864
01:02:20,450 --> 01:02:23,310
Yes. I pited you.
I saw how anxious you were.

865
01:02:23,400 --> 01:02:24,940
[-A fair face]
-That's her.

866
01:02:25,020 --> 01:02:26,870
[-may hide a foul heart.]
-I know right?

867
01:02:26,960 --> 01:02:28,760
[Are you curious about me?]

868
01:02:28,850 --> 01:02:31,360
Yes. I'm curious about you.


